		<section id="agents" class="mb-12">
			<div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
				<div class="i-lucide-bot w-6 h-6 text-accent-purple" />
				<h2 class="heading-2">Agents & Flows APIs</h2>
			</div>
			<p class="body-text mb-6">Execute agents, orchestration flows, and manage persistent sessions.</p>

			<!-- InvokeAgent -->
			<div class="card mb-6" id="invoke-agent">
				<div class="p-6 border-b border-surface-3">
					<h3 class="heading-3 mb-2">InvokeAgent</h3>
					<p class="body-text">Send a prompt to a Bedrock Agent. The agent reasons with ReAct, selects tools (action groups), queries knowledge bases, and returns a streamed response. Supports trace for debugging reasoning steps.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="p-6">
					<div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
						<div>
							<h4 class="caption font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide mb-3">When to use</h4>
							<ul class="space-y-2">
								<li class="flex items-start gap-2 body-text"><span class="text-accent-aqua">-</span>Autonomous task execution with tools</li>
								<li class="flex items-start gap-2 body-text"><span class="text-accent-aqua">-</span>Multi-step reasoning</li>
								<li class="flex items-start gap-2 body-text"><span class="text-accent-aqua">-</span>Customer service bots (KB + Lambda tools)</li>
								<li class="flex items-start gap-2 body-text"><span class="text-accent-aqua">-</span>Return of control (human-in-the-loop)</li>
							</ul>
						</div>
						<div>
							<h4 class="caption font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide mb-3">Key parameters</h4>
							<ul class="space-y-2">
								<li class="body-text"><span class="text-accent-yellow">agentId + agentAliasId</span> — the prepared agent version</li>
								<li class="body-text"><span class="text-accent-yellow">sessionId</span> — multi-turn conversations</li>
								<li class="body-text"><span class="text-accent-yellow">enableTrace</span> — see reasoning + tool calls</li>
								<li class="body-text"><span class="text-accent-yellow">sessionState</span> — pass context, return of control results</li>
							</ul>
						</div>
					</div>

					<h4 class="caption font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide mb-3">With trace analysis (debug agent reasoning)</h4>
					<div class="bg-surface-0 border border-surface-3 rounded-card p-4 overflow-x-auto">
						<pre class="text-sm text-ink-secondary font-mono leading-relaxed" set:text={codeInvokeAgent} />
					</div>

					<div class="bg-accent-aqua/5 border border-accent-aqua/20 rounded-card p-5 mt-6">
						<h4 class="heading-3 text-accent-aqua mb-3">Learn by Doing</h4>
						<ol class="space-y-2 body-text">
							<li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent-aqua font-bold">1.</span>Create an agent with a system prompt and one Lambda action group</li>
							<li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent-aqua font-bold">2.</span>Invoke with enableTrace=True and read the reasoning chain</li>
							<li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent-aqua font-bold">3.</span>Associate a knowledge base and test retrieval-augmented answers</li>
							<li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent-aqua font-bold">4.</span>Configure return of control for a human approval step</li>
						</ol>
						<div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
							<a href="https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/machine-learning/build-generative-ai-agents-with-amazon-bedrock-amazon-dynamodb-amazon-kendra-amazon-lex-and-langchain/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="badge border border-accent-blue text-accent-blue hover:bg-accent-blue/10">Blog: Building Agents</a>
							<a href="https://github.com/aws-samples/amazon-bedrock-workshop/tree/main/05_Agents" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="badge border border-accent-blue text-accent-blue hover:bg-accent-blue/10">Workshop: Agents</a>
						</div>
					</div>

					<div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
						<span class="badge-muted">Service: bedrock-agent-runtime</span>
						<span class="badge-muted">Streaming</span>
						<span class="badge-muted">Multi-turn</span>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<!-- InvokeFlow -->
			<div class="card mb-6" id="invoke-flow">
				<div class="p-6 border-b border-surface-3">
					<h3 class="heading-3 mb-2">InvokeFlow</h3>
					<p class="body-text">Execute a Bedrock Prompt Flow — visual, no-code workflows that chain prompts, conditions, and data transformations.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="p-6">
					<div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
						<div>
							<h4 class="caption font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide mb-3">When to use</h4>
							<ul class="space-y-2">
								<li class="flex items-start gap-2 body-text"><span class="text-accent-aqua">-</span>No-code prompt orchestration</li>
								<li class="flex items-start gap-2 body-text"><span class="text-accent-aqua">-</span>Conditional branching on model output</li>
								<li class="flex items-start gap-2 body-text"><span class="text-accent-aqua">-</span>Chaining prompts with data transformations</li>
							</ul>
						</div>
						<div>
							<h4 class="caption font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide mb-3">Exam trigger</h4>
							<p class="body-text text-accent-yellow">"no-code workflow" or "visual orchestration" = Bedrock Flows</p>
						</div>
					</div>

					<div class="bg-surface-0 border border-surface-3 rounded-card p-4 overflow-x-auto">
						<pre class="text-sm text-ink-secondary font-mono leading-relaxed" set:text={codeInvokeFlow} />
					</div>

					<div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
						<a href="https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/machine-learning/build-multi-step-ai-workflows-with-amazon-bedrock-flows/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="badge border border-accent-blue text-accent-blue hover:bg-accent-blue/10">Blog: Multi-step AI Workflows</a>
						<span class="badge-muted">Service: bedrock-agent-runtime</span>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<!-- Session Management -->
			<div class="card mb-6" id="sessions">
				<div class="p-6 border-b border-surface-3">
					<h3 class="heading-3 mb-2">Session Management</h3>
					<p class="body-text">Create and manage persistent sessions for agents. Sessions maintain conversation history and metadata across multiple InvokeAgent calls.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="p-6">
					<div class="bg-surface-0 border border-surface-3 rounded-card p-4 overflow-x-auto mb-4">
						<pre class="text-sm text-ink-secondary font-mono leading-relaxed" set:text={codeSessionMgmt} />
					</div>
					<div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
						<span class="badge-muted">CreateSession</span>
						<span class="badge-muted">GetSession</span>
						<span class="badge-muted">EndSession</span>
						<span class="badge-muted">DeleteSession</span>
						<span class="badge-muted">Service: bedrock-agent-runtime</span>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

