		<!-- MODEL CUSTOMIZATION                         -->
		<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
		<section id="customization" class="mb-12">
			<div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
				<div class="i-lucide-settings-2 w-6 h-6 text-accent-red" />
				<h2 class="heading-2">Model Customization APIs</h2>
			</div>
			<p class="body-text mb-6">Fine-tune or continue pre-training Bedrock models on your domain data. Requires provisioned throughput for inference.</p>

			<div class="card mb-6">
				<div class="p-6 border-b border-surface-3">
					<h3 class="heading-3 mb-2">CreateModelCustomizationJob / CreateProvisionedModelThroughput</h3>
					<p class="body-text">Submit a fine-tuning or continued pre-training job. After completion, provision throughput to serve the custom model.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="p-6">
					<div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
						<div>
							<h4 class="caption font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide mb-3">Fine-tuning vs continued pre-training</h4>
							<ul class="space-y-2">
								<li class="body-text"><span class="text-accent-aqua font-semibold">Fine-tuning</span> — labeled prompt-completion pairs (JSONL), task-specific</li>
								<li class="body-text"><span class="text-accent-aqua font-semibold">Continued pre-training</span> — unlabeled domain text, domain adaptation</li>
								<li class="body-text"><span class="text-accent-aqua font-semibold">Distillation</span> — train smaller model to mimic larger model's outputs</li>
							</ul>
						</div>
						<div>
							<h4 class="caption font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide mb-3">Exam triggers</h4>
							<p class="body-text text-accent-yellow">"labeled training data" + "managed" = Bedrock fine-tuning</p>
							<p class="body-text text-accent-yellow mt-2">"custom training scripts" or "LoRA adapters" = SageMaker</p>
							<p class="body-text text-accent-yellow mt-2">"unlabeled domain corpus" = continued pre-training</p>
						</div>
					</div>

					<div class="bg-surface-0 border border-surface-3 rounded-card p-4 overflow-x-auto">
						<pre class="text-sm text-ink-secondary font-mono leading-relaxed" set:text={codeCustomization} />
					</div>

					<div class="bg-accent-aqua/5 border border-accent-aqua/20 rounded-card p-5 mt-6">
						<h4 class="heading-3 text-accent-aqua mb-3">Learn by Doing</h4>
						<ol class="space-y-2 body-text">
							<li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent-aqua font-bold">1.</span>Prepare JSONL training data with 100+ prompt-completion pairs</li>
							<li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent-aqua font-bold">2.</span>Upload to S3 and create a customization job via console or API</li>
							<li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent-aqua font-bold">3.</span>Monitor training metrics (loss, validation accuracy)</li>
							<li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent-aqua font-bold">4.</span>Provision throughput and test the custom model</li>
							<li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent-aqua font-bold">5.</span>Compare custom model vs base model on your domain tasks</li>
						</ol>
						<div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
							<a href="https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/machine-learning/fine-tune-anthropics-claude-3-haiku-in-amazon-bedrock-to-boost-model-accuracy-and-quality/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="badge border border-accent-blue text-accent-blue hover:bg-accent-blue/10">Blog: Fine-tuning Claude Haiku</a>
							<a href="https://github.com/aws-samples/amazon-bedrock-workshop/tree/main/03_Model_customization" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="badge border border-accent-blue text-accent-blue hover:bg-accent-blue/10">Workshop: Model Customization</a>
						</div>
					</div>

					<div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
						<span class="badge-muted">Service: bedrock (control plane)</span>
						<span class="badge-muted">Async job</span>
						<span class="badge-muted">Provisioned throughput required</span>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

